>> source: https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/veggie-yaki-udon
>> time required: 25 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/yaki-udon-19d4efb.jpg?resize=768,574

Heat the @oil{1.5%tbsp} in a non-stick frying pan or wok over a high heat. Add the @onion{1} and fry for ~{5%min}s. Stir in the @mangetout{160%g}, @corn{70%g}, @pak choi{2} and @spring onions{3} and cook for ~{5%min}s more. Add the @garlic{1%large}, @curry powder{0.5%tbsp} and @soy sauce{4%tsp}, and cook for another minute.

Add the @udon noodles{300%g} along with the @ginger{1%tbsp} (if using) and reserved brine, and stir in 2-3 tbsp hot water until the noodles are heated through. Divide between bowls and serve.
